    • printTable

      public static void printTable​(java.lang.String[] fields, java.lang.String[] values)
      Prints the given provided fields and values in a table-like format.

      Each field and value are printed in pairs on each line, the format of which is specified in the sample output. See the example below. 

      
 Language:                 English
 Time Zone:                Pacific Standard Time
 Color:                    ANSI
 Standard Output Log:      ./src/assignment02PartB/log/StandardOut.log
 Default club:             SF Giants
      Parameters:
      fields - The array of strings as fields. The size of the array must be equal to those of values.
      values - The array of strings as values. The size of the array must be equal to those of fields.
